Commentary: OUT! CHOPPED ON! Shannon Gabriel gets his first wicket and what a session this has turned out to be for West Indies! Ajinkya Rahane is the latest casualty as he plays a really lazy shot before the break. This is bowled on a good length as well and in the channel outside the off stump. Ajinkya Rahane pokes at the ball with no real intent and gets an inside edge that goes on to shatter his stumps. Rahane looks stunned as India have lost their fourth wicket and have stumbled slightly after the strong start that they had. The hosts have come back really strong in this game and will be going into the dressing room with their tails up as it will be TEA of DAY 1!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A brilliant review from West Indies and it is Ravindra Jadeja who departs now! Kemar Roach ​​​​​​ comes from 'round the wicket and lands it full, angling in, outside off, Ravindra Jadeja goes for the drive away from the body and gets beaten on the outside edge. Joshua Da Silva pouches it safely and goes up in appeal. There was a sound as the ball went past the bat but the umpire is unmoved. The West Indies players are convinced that they have got their man and Kraigg Brathwaite goes for the review. The UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball is next to the bat. The on-field decision is overturned and West Indies have their 6th wicket.

Commentary: PLUMB! A successful review by West Indies and Mohammed Siraj has to depart! Jomel Warrican fires this one really full and outside off. Mohammed Siraj gets his front foot across the line of the stumps and loos to sweep this behind square on the leg side. He misses and gets hit on the pads which makes the West Indies players go up in appeal! The umpire remains unmoved and Kraigg Brathwaite decides to go upstairs for the review. UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved and Ball Tracking has three reds. They have another look to see if the ball has hit the front pad or the back to determine the point of contact. Looks like it has missed the front leg and hit him on the back pad. The on-field decision has to be reversed and India lose their ninth wicket.
Default_Commentary: 126.5: Jomel Warrican to Mohammed Siraj, OUT! lbw b Jomel Warrican.
Howout: lbw b Jomel Warrican

Commentary: OUT! Kemar Roach wraps up India's inning and Ravichandran Ashwin's good inning lower down the order comes to an end! This is bowled on a good length and at the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to make room and throws the kitchen sink at the ball but does not connect. The ball goes onto peg back the leg pole and India have been bowled out before Tea. They have got a decent total on the board but West Indies will be proud of their effort on a wicket that was conducive for the batters. It will also be TEA on DAY 2!

Commentary: OUT! MAIDEN TEST WICKET FOR MUKESH KUMAR! He has been rewarded for some tight bowling this morning and his hard work has paid off to the delight of his teammates! After consistently bowling full he pulls his length back slightly to a good length and offers width outside the off stump. Kirk Mckenzie looks to cut this one away but gets a faint edge through to the keeper. Ishan Kishan makes no mistake grabbing hold of the ball with his gloves and everyone runs towards the debutant. Celebrations all around for the Indian players as they desperately needed a breakthrough. West Indies lose their second wicket and will need to build a partnership once again as they still trail by 321 runs.
Default_Commentary: 51.4: Mukesh Kumar to Kirk Mckenzie, OUT! c Ishan Kishan b Mukesh Kumar.
Howout: c Ishan Kishan b Mukesh Kumar

Commentary: OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! A classic off-spinners dismissal as Ashwin goes through the defence of Brathwaite! Comes from over the wicket and floats it up, outside off, the ball pitches in the footmarks and spins in sharply. Kraigg Brathwaite is not fully forward to defend and pays the price. The ball goes through the gap between the bat and the pad to breach the defence. Takes the middle stump to signal the end of the West Indies skipper's resilience. A much-needed breakthrough for Rohit Sharma and Co as West Indies lose their third wicket.

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Mohammed Siraj has gone through Joshua Da Silva's defence here! Ishan Kishan had predicted this as the outcome as the rain looked to be arriving! It must have played on Joshua Da Silva's mind as he had no idea about this delivery. Mohammed Siraj bowls this on a good length and angles this in from outside off. The ball nips back in further off the surface and Joshua Da Silva is found pushing at this one away from his body. There is a massive gap between the bat and the pad as the ball creeps in and shatters the stumps. The West Indies wicketkeeper looks really disappointed here as he takes the long walk back to the shed! He looks up at the skies as it opens up and the rain comes pouring down. West Indies have lost half their side now and India find themselves back on top in this tie.
Default_Commentary: 97.2: Mohammed Siraj to Joshua Da Silva, OUT! b Mohammed Siraj.
Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: OUT! PLUMB! The change of angle has worked immediately for Ravichandran Ashwin as he takes his second wicket in quick succession! Goes over the wicket and floats this one full, pitching just outside off. The ball goes straight with the arm and Kirk Mckenzie is playing down the wrong line anticipating the ball to spin. The ball beats the inside edge and goes on to hit the pads right in front of the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin is celebrating instantly and the umpire also raises his finger. Mckenzie has a chat with Tagenarine Chanderpaul and they decide not to go for a review which is a good decision as this is as plumb as it can get. West Indies have lost their second wicket and are finding it difficult to handle the Indian spinners.
Default_Commentary: 19.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Kirk Mckenzie, OUT! lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin.
Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin
